alert.note: Alert for King (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued January 07 at 6:56PM PST until January 08 at 4:42PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Seattle WA has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Washington... Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County. .Heavy rain that fell across the region over the past 48 hours will continue to push the Snoqualmie River Near Carnation into minor flood stage tonight. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS EVENING THROUGH SATURDAY AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Snoqualmie River Near Carnation. * WHEN...Until tomorrow afternoon. * IMPACTS...At 54.0 feet, the Snoqualmie River will flood much of the farm land and several roads from Fall City downstream through Carnation and Duvall. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 6:15 PM PST Friday the stage was 53.7 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage this evening. It will then fall below flood stage late tonight to 47.7 feet Monday afternoon. - Flood stage is 54.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by late tonight at 300 AM PST.
